      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000090702,
      "SummaryText": "1.  POLICIES\n\n     --------------\n\n     \n\nA.  An accidental release of a regulated substance would be detected by strategically-located VOC monitors that would immediately alert production personnel.  All drums and cylinders are leakproof-tested after filling; all canisters are leak-tested each day of operation. All tank cars are physically disconnected, valved-off, and capped during off-hours.  Security fencing, cameras, and alarms exist throughout the entire production facility. Site periodically conducts Leak Detection And Repair monitoring (LDAR) for the Ethylene Oxide & Propylene Oxide connections, valves, etc., to  ensure no leakage of these substances.\n\n\n\nB.  An Emergency Action Plan has been prepared and submitted to the Colleton County Fire & Rescue Department and the LEPC specifying a response and warning system in the event of an accidental release of a regulated substance.  The facility also conducts quarterly evacuation drills according to the Emergency Action Plan.\n\n\n\n2.  STATIONARY SOURCE AND REGULATED SUBSTANCES\n\n     -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n\nA.  The primary activity is the repackaging of chemicals into drums, cylinders, and canisters for medical sterilization businesses and for synthesis customers.\n\n\n\nB.  The regulated substances are: \n\n           - Ethylene Oxide  \n\n           - Propylene Oxide   \n\n          \n\n3.  RELEASE SCENARIO\n\n    The Accidental release prevention is accomplished through the RMP/PSM elements with emphasis on Management of Change, Process Hazard Analysis, Pre-startup-Safety Review, Mechanical Integrity and Employee Training. The site production, tank farm areas are monitored with cameras, chemical sensors, fire detection, etc. \n\n    \n\n4.  PREVENTION\n\n     --------------------\n\n\n\nA.  The two regulated substances at the Green Pond plant are covered by the OSHA Process Safety Management (PSM) Standard. Drums, totes, Cannisters, rail cars, etc., comply with the DOT reg"
